WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.281 --> 00:00:02.991
Inventory management involves formulating

2
00:00:02.991 --> 00:00:05.373
and implementing inventory policies

3
00:00:05.373 --> 00:00:08.095
that support organizational goals.

4
00:00:08.095 --> 00:00:10.642
Inventory management activities include,

5
00:00:10.642 --> 00:00:12.507
but are not always limited to,

6
00:00:12.507 --> 00:00:17.048
forecasting, demand planning, and control activities.

7
00:00:17.048 --> 00:00:20.403
Inventory managers use end item forecasts

8
00:00:20.403 --> 00:00:23.889
such as sales, production, or maintenance forecasts

9
00:00:23.889 --> 00:00:27.362
to derive forecasts for individual item numbers.

10
00:00:27.362 --> 00:00:29.333
They formulate inventory rules

11
00:00:29.333 --> 00:00:32.489
that affect safety stock levels, lot sizes,

12
00:00:32.489 --> 00:00:34.065
and replenishment lead times

13
00:00:34.065 --> 00:00:37.012
in order to support anticipated demand.

14
00:00:37.012 --> 00:00:40.661
Additionally, they manage or control item inventories

15
00:00:40.661 --> 00:00:43.664
according to the established inventory rules.

16
00:00:43.664 --> 00:00:46.715
An example of inventory management in industry

17
00:00:46.715 --> 00:00:49.602
includes Walmart maintaining distribution centers

18
00:00:49.602 --> 00:00:52.067
to manage and send goods to their stores.

